comments: Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in Conley's (UTA) path with his hand against Conley's (UTA) arm and marginal contact occurs as Conley (UTA) defends under the pick.
Sabonis (SAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Huerter's (SAC) arm is not in a vertical position when contact occurs with Clarkson's (UTA) arm, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Barnes (SAC) establishes himself in Clarkson's (UTA) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Huerter (SAC) and Clarkson (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Clarkson (UTA) immediately slides his hand off of Sabonis's (SAC) side and marginal contact occurs during the handoff.
Clarkson (UTA) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Huerter's (SAC) arm after the release.
Sabonis (SAC) makes marginal contact with Kessler (UTA) as he secures the loose ball.
Huerter (SAC) and Markkanen (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Markkanen (UTA) establishes himself in Murray's (SAC) path and absorbs the contact.
Murray (SAC) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Markkanen's (UTA) wrist after the release.
Olynyk (UTA) brings his arm to Fox's (SAC) front and marginal contact occurs during Fox's (SAC) drive.
Fox (SAC) and Clarkson (UTA) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Huerter (SAC) is not established in a legal guarding position in Markkanen's (UTA) path when contact occurs and he is not dislodged from his position by the marginal contact.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in Conley's (UTA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Fox (SAC) commits a take foul on Conley (UTA).
Sabonis (SAC) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Conley (UTA) during the pick.
Sabonis (SAC) briefly grasps Kessler's (UTA) arm as he jumps towards the rim and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Fox (SAC) makes contact with the ball and the contact with Markkanen's (UTA) arm as both players attempt to control the rebound is marginal.

Fox (SAC) brushes Olynyk's (UTA) head and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Markkanen (UTA) legally contests Huerter's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Barnes (SAC) rests his hands on Markkanen (UTA) during the throw-in and the contact is marginal.
Clarkson (UTA) slightly extends his arm to Fox's (SAC) front during the screen and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Fox (SAC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Markkanen (UTA) prior to incidental arm contact occurring during the drive.
Barnes (SAC) and Markkanen (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Barnes (SAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes OOB.
Markkanen (UTA) brings his off-arm toward Barnes (SAC) and marginal contact occurs as Markkanen (UTA) releases away without applying any force.
Barnes (SAC) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Markkanen's (UTA) arm after the release.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the game clock is reset to 00:00.4.
Olynyk (UTA) and Fox (SAC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Sabonis (SAC) engages with Markkanen (UTA) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Sabonis (SAC) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Mitchell (SAC) grasps Sexton's (UTA) arm and immediately releases it. Sexton draws attention to the marginal contact but is not dislodged from his rebounding position.
Olynyk (UTA) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly awarded to SAC.
